# Environment and secrets — these patterns are belt-and-suspenders against
# accidental redistribution. The publish step in the stack-test workflow
# also runs a runtime assertion (scripts/check/no-secrets-in-image.sh)
# against the candidate image before pushing to GHCR; both layers must
# stay in sync.
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
**/id_rsa
**/id_rsa.*
**/id_ed25519
**/id_ed25519.*
**/credentials
**/credentials.*
**/secrets
**/secrets.*

# Project-specific
examples.txt
WORKTREE.md
CLAUDE.md
compose/

# Keep essential files
!pyproject.toml
!README.md
!LICENSE
!src/
!scripts/cache/
!examples/config.example.*
!docker/
